<CaseStudy
  title="Charac: NHS-Integrated Pharmacy Analytics"
  description="Built the Power BI and GA4 analytics layer for one of the UK's fastest-growing pharmacy platforms, turning prescription, delivery and consultation data into self-serve KPIs for pharmacy owners and driving acquisition on the patient app."
  role="Data Analyst · Commercial Project"
  period="2024"
  stack={['Power BI', 'DAX', 'GA4', 'SQL', 'Python', 'ETL/ELT', 'GDPR / NHS IG']}
  outcome="End-to-end analytics layer across the patient app and pharmacy owner portal: prescription KPIs, delivery tracking, consultation funnel, and acquisition cohorts."
  liveUrl="https://charac.co.uk"
>

  <h2>The question</h2>
  <p>
    Charac sits at the intersection of consumer health tech and NHS infrastructure. Pharmacy owners need real-time visibility into prescription volumes, delivery SLAs, and consultation demand; the growth team needs acquisition and retention signals from the patient app. The data existed across disparate sources with no unified reporting layer.
  </p>
  <p>
    The brief: build analytics that pharmacy owners can actually use without a data team behind them, while giving growth stakeholders the product metrics to make acquisition decisions.
  </p>

  <h2>The approach</h2>
  <h3>Data modelling</h3>
  <p>
    Mapped the core entities (patient, prescription, pharmacy, delivery, consultation) and built a clean SQL layer that joined operational data to behavioural signals. ETL pipelines pulled from the platform backend and landed data in a schema structured for Power BI's DirectQuery model, keeping KPIs fresh without the latency of scheduled refreshes.
  </p>

  <h3>Power BI layer</h3>
  <p>
    Designed a pharmacy-owner-facing dashboard with three views: <strong>Prescription Hub</strong> (volume, status, fulfilment SLA), <strong>Delivery Tracker</strong> (on-time rate, exception flags), and <strong>Consultation Demand</strong> (booking trends, capacity vs. demand). DAX measures were written to handle NHS calendar quirks (bank holidays, bank holiday prescription patterns) and to surface actionable exceptions: pharmacies falling below SLA thresholds surface immediately at the top of their view.
  </p>
  <p>
    The growth team received a separate executive view: acquisition funnel, patient retention cohorts, and channel attribution from GA4.
  </p>

  <h3>GA4 implementation</h3>
  <p>
    Audited and extended the existing GA4 setup, defining a clean event taxonomy for the patient app (prescription requests, delivery tracking opens, consultation bookings), validated the data layer, and connected GA4 export to the Power BI acquisition model via BigQuery. This enabled end-to-end attribution from acquisition channel through to first prescription fulfilled.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>GDPR / NHS IG consideration:</strong> Charac operates as a data processor under NHS Information Governance requirements. All analytics work was scoped to aggregated, pseudonymised data. No patient-identifiable information touched the BI layer, a constraint that shaped every modelling decision.</p>
  </div>

